# get expression data frame
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.stats import linregress

# Select a gene of interest
gene = "BMP4"  # Replace with your gene of interest

# Extract pseudotime, expression, and celltype information
pseudotime = adata_sampled.obs['latent_time_new']
pseudotime = (pseudotime - pseudotime.min()) / (pseudotime.max() - pseudotime.min())
expression = adata_sampled[:, gene].X.toarray().flatten()  # Convert sparse to dense
cell_types = adata_sampled.obs['celltype']  # Cell type annotation

# Combine all data into a single dataframe
plot_df = pd.DataFrame({
    "Pseudotime": pseudotime,
    "Expression": expression,
    "CellType": cell_types
})

# Drop NaN values (if any pseudotime or expression is missing)
plot_df = plot_df.dropna()

# Sort the dataframe by Pseudotime
plot_df = plot_df.sort_values("Pseudotime")

# Perform polynomial regression (e.g., degree=2)
coeffs = np.polyfit(plot_df["Pseudotime"], plot_df["Expression"], deg=5)
poly_fit = np.poly1d(coeffs)

# Scatter plot with polynomial fit
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
sns.scatterplot(
    data=plot_df,
    x="Pseudotime",
    y="Expression",
    hue="CellType",
    palette="Set2",
    alpha=0.8
)
plt.plot(plot_df["Pseudotime"], poly_fit(plot_df["Pseudotime"]), color="black", label="Polynomial fit (degree 5)")
plt.title(f"Expression trend of {gene}")
plt.xlabel("Pseudotime")
plt.ylabel("Normalized Expression")
plt.legend(title="Cell Type", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc="upper left")
plt.grid(False)
plt.show()

import os
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Define the list of genes of interest (example)
gene_list = cytokine_chemokine_intersected_genes

# Find the intersection of the genes with adata_sampled.var_names
intersected_genes = list(set(gene_list).intersection(adata_sampled.var_names))

# Create an output directory for the PDF files (optional)
output_dir = "figures/gene_expression_plot"
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)

# Normalize pseudotime
pseudotime = adata_sampled.obs['latent_time_new']
pseudotime = (pseudotime - pseudotime.min()) / (pseudotime.max() - pseudotime.min())

# Extract cell type information
cell_types = adata_sampled.obs['celltype']  # Cell type annotation

# Loop through each intersected gene
for gene in intersected_genes:
    # Extract expression values for the current gene
    expression = adata_sampled[:, gene].X.toarray().flatten()  # Convert sparse to dense
    
    # Combine all data into a single dataframe
    plot_df = pd.DataFrame({
        "Pseudotime": pseudotime,
        "Expression": expression,
        "CellType": cell_types
    })

    # Drop NaN values (if any pseudotime or expression is missing)
    plot_df = plot_df.dropna()

    # Sort the dataframe by Pseudotime
    plot_df = plot_df.sort_values("Pseudotime")

    # Perform polynomial regression (e.g., degree=5)
    coeffs = np.polyfit(plot_df["Pseudotime"], plot_df["Expression"], deg=5)
    poly_fit = np.poly1d(coeffs)

    # Create the plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
    sns.scatterplot(
        data=plot_df,
        x="Pseudotime",
        y="Expression",
        hue="CellType",
        palette="Set2",
        alpha=0.8
    )
    plt.plot(
        plot_df["Pseudotime"], 
        poly_fit(plot_df["Pseudotime"]), 
        color="black", 
        label="Polynomial fit (degree 5)"
    )
    plt.title(f"Expression trend of {gene}")
    plt.xlabel("Pseudotime")
    plt.ylabel("Normalized Expression")
    plt.legend(title="Cell Type", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc="upper left")
    plt.grid(False)

    # Save the plot to a PDF file
    output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, f"{gene}.pdf")
    plt.savefig(output_path, format="pdf", bbox_inches="tight")

    # Close the plot to free memory
    plt.close()

print(f"Plots saved in the directory: {output_dir}")

Plots saved in the directory: figures/gene_expression_plot
